President of the Senate, Ahmad Lawan; Secretary to the Government of the Federation(SGF), Boss Mustapha; Former Senate President, Anyim Pius Anyim; Senator representing Ebonyi North, Sam Egwu; and other prominent Nigerians from walks of life, at the weekend, paid tribute to Late Ezinne Eunice Nnachi, mother of Senator Michael Ama Nnachi representing Ebonyi South zone. Ezinne Nnachi died at the age of 87 and was buried in her husband’s country home, Itim Edda, Afikpo South local government area of Ebonyi State at the weekend. Lawan in his message said the late matriarch lived a good life, left enduring legacies and served God and her community with solemn piety and dedication, adding that posterity would remember her kindly. Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha in his tribute, opined that the late matriarch lived a fulfilled and accomplished life worthy of praise. “Her dedication to service of God and humanity, unparalleled commitment to the growth of others and the impartation of high moral principles are inarguable and highly commendable. “She will not be forgotten in a hurry as she had succeeded in nurturing the gentlemen and ladies amongst her offspring, siblings, relations, children and grandchildren who have turned out to be great men and women in our society today”, he said. Anyim, former Secretary to the government of the federation and 2023 presidential aspirant on the platform of the PDP who was represented by Hon Livinus Makwe, on his part said Ezinne Nnachi who was a multi-trader and successful farmer, lived exemplary life and accomplishments and urged the children to take solace in the legacies she left behind. On his part, Senator Egwu representing Ebonyi North senatorial district, said “as a matriarch, she impacted many lives and made remarkable contributions towards the development of her community. Her death has therefore created a significant vacuum, especially at this time when her motherly counsel is needed most”. POLL Other dignitaries who attended the burial include: Sen Enoh representing Cross River Central; Sen Obinna Joseph Ọgba representing Ebonyi Central; Senator Abba Moro, Senator Jaribe, Chief Gideon Chidiebere Osi, High Chief Julius Awa Oji, Hon Ugoji Ama Oti, Chief Clement Ifeanyichukwu Okorie (Oloye) and Engr Fidelis Nwankwo, former Minister of Health for State; among other Federal Lawmakers